    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Upper Kedron?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Upper Kedron values are driven primarily by block size and the semi-rural character of the property. Large acreage-style blocks with genuine privacy, rural feel and space command the strongest premiums. Properties close to D'Aguilar National Park or with established tree cover and genuine separation from neighbours consistently attract the strongest buyer interest. The connection to the Ferny Grove State High School catchment also draws family buyers, and the suburb's position within Brisbane City Council while retaining semi-rural character supports long-term price resilience.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Upper Kedron?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Upper Kedron properties typically sell within 30 to 50 days. The buyer pool is focused: these are buyers who have specifically decided they want an acreage lifestyle within Brisbane's boundary. When the right buyer appears, the decision process is often fast because they have already resolved the trade-off between space and commute distance. Properties that genuinely deliver on the semi-rural promise attract faster campaigns than those that do not.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Upper Kedron?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Upper Kedron offers the most genuinely semi-rural character of any suburb within Brisbane's city boundary in the outer northern corridor. Large blocks, elevated terrain, quiet streets and direct adjacency to D'Aguilar National Park give residents a lifestyle that feels more rural than the postcode suggests. Keperra and Ferny Grove stations provide rail access for commuting days, and the suburb remains within Brisbane City Council for services. Popular with owner-occupier families and lifestyle buyers who want genuine space and privacy within the metropolitan area.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Upper Kedron a good suburb to sell in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Upper Kedron has maintained consistent demand from buyers seeking the acreage lifestyle within Brisbane's metropolitan boundary. The suburb's semi-rural character is difficult to replicate at an equivalent price point in more central areas, and as working-from-home patterns have made outer-ring locations more viable for a broader range of buyers, the pool of buyers willing to trade commute time for space has grown. Well-presented homes with genuine block size and rural character attract buyers who have been actively searching for exactly what Upper Kedron offers.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

